# Cursor Rules Index

This is the main index rule that helps navigate to specific guidelines based on the task at hand.

## When to Use Each Rule

### For UI/Design Tasks
- **Reference**: [ui-patterns.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/ui-patterns.mdc)
- **Use when**: Creating components, styling, implementing design patterns, working with Tailwind CSS, dark mode, responsive design

### For Infrastructure/Deployment Tasks
- **Reference**: [infrastructure-guide.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/infrastructure-guide.mdc)
- **Use when**: Docker setup, deployment, environment configuration, build processes, container management

### For Development Standards
- **Reference**: [development-guidelines.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/development-guidelines.mdc)
- **Use when**: Writing code, following TypeScript standards, React/Next.js patterns, file organization

### For Project Context
- **Reference**: [project-overview.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/project-overview.mdc)
- **Use when**: Understanding project structure, technology stack, overall architecture

